			<pb n="3"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; <date>June 29&#44; 1854</date>.</p>
				<p><sic><addressee>Rev. Isaac Lesser</addressee></sic>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44;</p>
				<p>Peace&#44; as usual&#44; most honored friend&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please send an &#8220;Occident&#8221; to <persName>Mr. Joseph Levy</persName>&#44; <placeName>Honesdale&#44;<lb/> Pa.</placeName>  If you want to&#44; <persName>Mr. Levy</persName> will pay you the &#36;3. in advance&#44; but<lb/> there is no need for it.  The man is reliable.  I am surprised that<lb/> you have not replied to my last <sic>latter</sic>&#44; either to myself or to <persName>Mr.<lb/> Michaelson</persName>.  Even if the reply be a refusal&#44; the said man wants to<lb/> have it&#44; in order to come before the trustees with clean hands&#44; that<lb/> he has written for it.  I sent you my own and <persName>Michaelson&#39;s</persName> letter&#44; <sic>t</sic><lb/> through <persName>Frankel</persName>&#44; <placeName>13 North Street&#44; Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">With all respect&#44; I sign in friendliness&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Michael</persName> son of <persName>Rabbi Abraham Uri</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Michael Light</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>42 Oliver Street</placeName></p>
		</body>
